               <msContents>
                  <summary>Documentary text from Egypt, written on papyrus. Papyrus belongs to the archive of Ammon, the well-known scholastikos, or lawyer. Recto has a another documentary text in Greek (P.Duk.inv. 227 R)</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Dimensions of fragments are 3.9 x 3.3 cm. or smaller</note>
                     <note type="general">3 lines</note>
                     <note type="general">Written across the fibers on the verso in Ammon's hand; written along the fibers on the recto in a different hand and inverse to the text on the recto</note>
                     <note type="general">P.Duk.inv. 227 V was formerly P.Duk.inv. G 227 V</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
